# Git mailmap — canonicalize author identities for the docs.
#
# This file lives at the PROJECT ROOT as `.mailmap`. `git log --use-mailmap`,
# the mkdocs-document-dates plugin, and hooks/submodule_authors.py all read it
# to dedupe the author list shown at the bottom of each docs page — so the same
# person committing under several names/emails shows up once.
#
# Format (see `man gitmailmap`):
#   Canonical Name <canonical@email> <other@email>
#   Canonical Name <canonical@email> Other Name <other@email>
#
# Example — collapse a personal email and a GitHub no-reply email into one
# canonical identity (delete this and add your own team):
#
# Jane Doe <jane.doe@example.com> <jane@personal.example>
# Jane Doe <jane.doe@example.com> <12345+janedoe@users.noreply.github.com>
